5:
Wow, look at all the pretty
decorations! What's the occasion?
8:
The Valentine's Fest is coming up. It's
a festival where we all eat sweets
together.
11:
Ohh, I get it! Sweets do taste extra
yummy this time of year... That kinda
reminds me of Fioletovy Den.
14:
Ah, that's a festival in my hometown
where you give homemade sweets
to people you're close to.
21:
Um, Alk, Stella... could I also
celebrate the Valentine's Fest?
26:
Of course! It's a festival, after all.
They're meant to be enjoyed by
everyone.
30:
Yay! In that case, I'm going to make
something for everyone, just like I
used to do for Fioletovy Den!
46:
Hey, why is everyone in this town a
terrible cook except for you, Alk?
52:
Well, this is why I bought extra
ingredients! Once I clean up this
mess, we'll try again!
56: And I will be here to help.
60:
...H-hey, by the way, what exactly
are you making?
65:
Just something I found while
exploring the shops in Palpebra.
What was the name again...
69:
It's a type of biscuit cookie. Boh?
Boo? I'm not sure how to pronounce
it.
73: C-could you show me the recipe?
76:
Um... The only thing written here is
the name and what I can only guess
is a drawing of the dessert...
80:
I-I'm sorry! They said the recipe is a
secret, so I figured I would just wing
it...
85:
Floretta... Baking is a science.
Nothing good will come of going in
blind.
90: I-I'm sorry! I won't do it again!
94:
You don't need to go all out for this
festival. Why not just make
something you already know how to
cook?
98:
Um, well... To be honest, I'm not the
most skilled person in the kitchen, so
there's not much I CAN make.
102:
Ah, but I think even I could handle
baranki.
106:
Baranki? I've never heard of those.
Are they a type of sweet?
109:
Yes, they're well-known in my
hometown.
112:
Ahaha... I used to make them all the
time with my friend as a kid. They're
a little plain, though.
117: Floretta... I would like to try baranki.
121: Oh, okay... I'll do my best.
126: Um, here you go... How do they taste?
130:
Mmm! These are delicious! It's like a
chocolate bagel.
135: I knew you could do it, Floretta.
139:
Huh? Ahaha... Aww, come on, I didn't
do anything fancy...
143:
Seriously, these are good. Just
accept the compliment and be
happy about it.
149:
I am happy! I just... I'm not used to all
this praise, so I'm not sure how to
react!
154: Floretta, you should have one too.
158:
Ah, right. Everyone eats sweets
together during the Valentine's Fest,
don't they?
162:
...Now this brings back memories of
my hometown.
166:
You're from a volcanic island in the
northern seas, right? Ever gone back?
170:
Nope. I haven't returned since I left
the island as a pup.
173:
...My friend was really good at
making baranki. They're the one who
taught me how to make them.
177:
Gotcha... What about paying them a
visit?
182:
I suppose I do want to see them
again. They were the only person
who wanted to be my friend back
then.
185:
They're not the only person I miss,
though... I wonder how the captain
and my former crewmates are
doing...
189:
Ahaha, my bad! I shouldn't be so
mopey during the festival!
192:
Why not go see them then? It's not
like they're impossible to reach.
195: After all, it's Fioletovy Den, isn't it?
200:
Oh yeah... We could all eat sweets
together...
204:
Um... You know, I think I WOULD like to
share these baranki with everyone
who's helped me so far.
212:
Sounds good to me. I'll even help out
with the baking.
219:
Operation: Happy Valentine's Fest is
a go!
